  "texts": [
    "The \"almost consumer goods\" characteristic evokes approaches deploying algorithms (what else should be more attractive for AI?!",
    "), parameters pre-definition, and patterns in the design process.",
    "One of the first authors and researchers active in this field was Makoto Sei Watanabe already in the 1990s (Leach, 2018c); however, having focused on machine-aided design rather than on analyses and the use of patterns, he remained unsatisfied with what AI was able to deliver in terms of design compared to the intuition of the (human) architect.",
    "Others, like Immanuel Goh or Andrea Banzi searched for explicit rules-scripting-based design generators working with inferred rules drawn from the dataset of samples.",
    "Not a patterns´ assessment and appropriation, but recognizing the internal logic of the pattern, and then extrapolating a broader design based on that logic that could potentially continue forever... (Leach, 2018d) in reality failing to contribute to the design practice eventually."
  ],
